dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
G. Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR-10 is a dataset containing 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 different classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
G. Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR-100 is a dataset containing 60,000 32x32 color images in 100 different classes, with 600 images per class. It is used for more fine-grained image classification tasks compared to CIFAR-10.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:creator: Z. Liu
P. Luo

X. Tang
dcterms:description: CelebA is a large-scale face attributes dataset with over 200,000 celebrity images, annotated with 40 attribute labels. It is widely used for tasks related to facial recognition and attribute classification.
dcterms:title: CelebA

dcterms:description: ImageNet is a large-scale hierarchical image database containing over 14 million images across 20,000 categories. It is primarily used for training and benchmarking image classification models.
dcterms:title: ImageNet
